title: Drawing, "End Table", ca. 1929–30
medium: Graphite on tracing paper, ruled border in graphite
markings: Stamp in black ink at lower left: DONALD DESKEY/ 145 WEST 57TH STREET/ NEW YORK CITY
inscribed: Inscribed in graphite in lower right margin: SCALE 1 1/2"=1'0"/7724 [circled]; lower right margin in red color pencil: P
description: Perspective, plan, and elevation drawing of end table of burled wood and darker wood at base. Rounded front edges and squared back edges. Drawer with no pull at top of table; two open shelves below.
